<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2876&amp;p=13562#p13562"><![CDATA[
That is why the commands are in a submenu so the user doesn't shutdown or restart by mistake.<br /><br />Also, for Windows 7 style of the menu, you can use the command called &quot;Shutdown....&quot; as the default Shutdown command. It shows a confirmation dialog with all the restart options.<br /><br />If you are using the Classic Style of the menu, the same command is called shutdown_box.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Jun 26, 2014 1:12 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
